    <item>
      <title>Hostname rename</title>
      <link>https://pidov.github.io/TIL/linux/rename-hostname/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 19 Nov 2016 16:02:39 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://pidov.github.io/TIL/linux/rename-hostname/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Edit the hostname in /etc/hostname using a text editor&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo vim /etc/hostname
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Delete the the old name and setup new. Save the file
Next edit the hosts file:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo vim /etc/hosts
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Replace all occurances of the old hostname with the new and save the file.
Finally reboot:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;sudo reboot
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>iptables</title>
      <link>https://pidov.github.io/TIL/linux/iptables/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Nov 2016 00:17:50 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://pidov.github.io/TIL/linux/iptables/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;h4 id=&#34;list-all-active-iptables-rulese-by-specification&#34;&gt;List all active iptables rulese by specification&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;iptables -S
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&#34;add-a-simple-rule&#34;&gt;Add a simple rule&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;iptables -A INPUT -m state --state NEW,ESTABLISHED,RELATED -j ACCEPT
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&#34;save-the-rules&#34;&gt;Save the rules&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;/sbin/service iptables save
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
</description>
